Our team provides quality assurance for mobile games developed by the company. We work closely with game designers, developers, and product stakeholders to ensure high quality, stability, and an engaging player experience across different mobile devices and operating system versions.

We continuously improve our QA processes step by step, focusing on efficient testing practices and product quality.

We are looking for a Manual QA team member who can perform manual testing of mobile games across different devices and operating system versions.

We work remotely, with formal meetings kept to a minimum ‚Äî one weekly stand-up, and the rest scheduled based on work needs.

Our focus is on maintaining a balance between game quality and business goals to ensure long-term project sustainability and a positive team atmosphere.

We strive to deliver games that we can truly be proud of :)

### Requirements

* 1+ year of experience in manual QA, preferably in the iGaming industry;

* Experience in testing mobile applications on real devices and emulators;

* Good problem-solving and debugging skills, with the ability to investigate and clearly describe issues;

* Basic understanding of CI/CD processes;

* Familiarity with Agile development processes;

* Confident knowledge of Jira, TestRail, Confluence, Postman, and basic Unix shell commands;

* Basic understanding of containerization technologies (e.g., Docker) is a plus;

* English level: Intermediate;

* Technical education background.

#### Responsibilities

* Communicate with product owners and developers to ensure alignment with project goals;
* Participate in product development activities from early stages, providing QA feedback;
* Identify, document, and track bugs throughout the development process;
* Develop and maintain test cases, checklists, and bug reports;
* Test the product across different mobile devices and operating system versions;
* Collaborate effectively within the team, maintaining a proactive and results-driven approach;
* Ensure accuracy, responsibility, and attention to detail in all testing activities.

